The paper deals with the complexity of monotone circuits, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The shift operator is a fundamental operation in computer science and is related to data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms (cs.DM). The use of logarithmic factors in the complexity analysis suggests that information theory (cs.IT) may be relevant. Finally, the study of monotone circuits is also related to machine learning and computational learning theory (cs.LG).
